2026-03-27T06:32:56.2956440Z Also=, or Alias= settings in the [Install] section, and DefaultInstance= for
2026-03-27T06:32:56.2957424Z template units). This means they are not meant to be enabled or disabled using systemctl.
2026-03-27T06:32:56.2958045Z  
2026-03-27T06:32:56.2958379Z Possible reasons for having these kinds of units are:
2026-03-27T06:32:56.2959446Z • A unit may be statically enabled by being symlinked from another unit's
2026-03-27T06:32:56.2960160Z   .wants/, .requires/, or .upholds/ directory.
2026-03-27T06:32:56.2960942Z • A unit's purpose may be to act as a helper for some other unit which has
2026-03-27T06:32:56.2961641Z   a requirement dependency on it.
2026-03-27T06:32:56.2962377Z • A unit may be started when needed via activation (socket, path, timer,
2026-03-27T06:32:56.2963140Z   D-Bus, udev, scripted systemctl call, ...).
2026-03-27T06:32:56.2964177Z • In case of template units, the unit is meant to be enabled with some
2026-03-27T06:32:56.2969880Z   instance name specified.
